    "title": "Eclipse",
    "description": "&quot;Vi Veri Vniversum Vivus Vici&quot;\n[By the force of truth I have conquered the universe.]\n– Anonymous Latin motto\n\n&quot;In a race, the quickest runner can never overtake the slowest, since the pursuer must first reach the point whence the pursued started, so that the slower must always hold a lead.&quot;\n– Zeno of Elea's dichotomy paradox as recounted by Aristotle.\n\n&quot;One luminary clock against the sky\nProclaimed the time was neither wrong nor right.&quot;\n– Robert Frost, 'Acquainted with the Night' (1928).\n\n&quot;With curious art the brain, too finely wrought,\nPreys on herself, and is destroy'd by thought:\nConstant attention wears the active mind,\nBlots out our powers, and leaves a blank behind.&quot;\n– Charles Churchill  (July 1763).",
